16/06/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg's government enjoys steady public support, according to a survey released Wednesday (16 June) by the MBMD agency.
The poll, conducted in April, found that about 30 per cent of the public believes the present coalition government is doing a better job than the previous Union of Democratic Forces cabinet.
Another 53 per cent do not approve of early elections.
The survey also registered an increase of public trust in the current government by 4 percentage points from March to 23 per cent in April.
Saxe-Coburg's rating improved by 3 percentage points to 25 per cent in April.
(Trud - 16/06/04)
